1
00:00:00,706 --> 00:00:03,008
I asked you nicely.

2
00:00:03,008 --> 00:00:04,877
I asked you to stop.

3
00:00:12,685 --> 00:00:13,986
Nope.

4
00:00:13,986 --> 00:00:15,864
Don't cross the line.

5
00:00:15,864 --> 00:00:17,689
That's enough.

6
00:00:21,060 --> 00:00:23,037
- Who do you think you are?
- Me?

7
00:00:23,037 --> 00:00:26,332
Just think of me as a guardian angel that woke up from a nap.

8
00:00:27,033 --> 00:00:28,544
Unconditioned response.

9
00:00:28,568 --> 00:00:32,081
You subconsciously close your eyes when an object suddenly approaches.

10
00:00:32,081 --> 00:00:34,940
It's an innate response to a stimulus.

11
00:00:41,214 --> 00:00:42,925
Stop it, you psycho.

12
00:00:42,925 --> 00:00:45,484
You could really get hurt doing that.

13
00:00:48,554 --> 00:00:49,465
Damn it.

14
00:00:49,489 --> 00:00:51,657
You should've listened to me.

15
00:00:52,225 --> 00:00:54,926
You can't tell me what to do.

16
00:01:02,869 --> 00:01:04,469
What's going on?

17
00:01:13,579 --> 00:01:15,614
Put that back down!

18
00:01:15,614 --> 00:01:18,317
What do you think you're doing?

19
00:01:18,317 --> 00:01:20,552
Jeez. Teach,

20
00:01:20,552 --> 00:01:22,831
I was just trying to stop a fight,

21
00:01:22,831 --> 00:01:25,491
but I almost got hurt by this chair.

22
00:01:25,491 --> 00:01:27,158
I'm so sorry.

23
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:29,760
Apologize to her.

24
00:01:33,332 --> 00:01:35,032
Quickly!

25
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:08,350
[Park Ji Hoon]

26
00:02:08,350 --> 00:02:11,130
[Choi Hyeon Wook]

27
00:02:11,130 --> 00:02:13,770
[Hong Kyeong]

28
00:02:13,770 --> 00:02:15,730
[Lee Yeon]

29
00:02:15,730 --> 00:02:17,840
[Shin Seung Ho]

30
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:21,470
[WEAK HERO CLASS 1]
♫ The heart that you take out after passing ♫

31
00:02:21,470 --> 00:02:24,230
♫ It's an old regret ♫

32
00:02:24,230 --> 00:02:28,440
♫ It's already too late ♫

33
00:02:30,230 --> 00:02:33,200
♫ Words I didn't want to hear ♫

34
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:36,200
♫ A face covered with a hand ♫

35
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:40,840
♫ I didn't know I'd miss you ♫

36
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:53,020
♫ I regret it, let's not cry anymore ♫

37
00:02:53,020 --> 00:03:05,680
♫ Sigh. Please don't hide ♫

38
00:03:09,660 --> 00:03:13,250
[Original: SeoPass - Kim Jin Seok "Weak Hero"]

39
00:03:15,968 --> 00:03:19,314
[Jeongjin Seoul Hospital]

40
00:03:19,314 --> 00:03:21,138
Yes.

41
00:03:21,138 --> 00:03:23,508
Yes. We're at the hospital now.

42
00:03:25,745 --> 00:03:28,080
All right. I'll do my best.

43
00:03:28,981 --> 00:03:30,816
Yes, don't worry.

44
00:03:31,684 --> 00:03:33,685
I'll call you later.

45
00:03:34,487 --> 00:03:36,388
Who do you think you are?

46
00:03:37,023 --> 00:03:38,500
Ma'am, please calm down.

47
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:41,760
I told you to bring your mom. Where is she?

48
00:03:43,396 --> 00:03:44,306
I'm sorry.

49
00:03:44,306 --> 00:03:47,532
I don't need your apology. Bring your mom.

50
00:03:48,935 --> 00:03:50,936
I don't have a mom.

51
00:03:50,937 --> 00:03:52,737
Are you kidding me?

52
00:03:52,737 --> 00:03:54,016
You listen to me.

53
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:57,443
I'm going to send you to juvenile detention.

54
00:04:04,050 --> 00:04:09,618
Yeongbin made a kid in our class stick this on my neck.

55
00:04:09,618 --> 00:04:11,422
What is that?

56
00:04:12,758 --> 00:04:15,260
- The thing is...
- Narcotics.

57
00:04:15,260 --> 00:04:16,828
That's what this is.

58
00:04:18,030 --> 00:04:20,199
What are you talking about?

59
00:04:20,199 --> 00:04:21,777
Where's your evidence?

60
00:04:21,777 --> 00:04:24,203
Do you have proof that I did it?

61
00:04:24,203 --> 00:04:26,638
Read the room.

62
00:04:26,638 --> 00:04:29,007
This is your bag, right?

63
00:04:31,277 --> 00:04:35,348
[Narcotic]
[Fentanyl]

64
00:04:41,921 --> 00:04:45,758
You realize this is far too serious for disciplinary action, right?

65
00:04:47,393 --> 00:04:51,129
I think a transfer will be the best move for Yeongbin.

66
00:04:53,666 --> 00:04:57,734
If this gets out, things will get bad.

67
00:04:58,571 --> 00:05:01,139
It's best we handle this quietly.

68
00:05:31,003 --> 00:05:32,971
Welcome home, son.

69
00:05:33,506 --> 00:05:35,940
Sieun, what happened to your hand?

70
00:05:36,907 --> 00:05:39,644
I hurt myself in gym class today.

71
00:05:39,644 --> 00:05:41,479
Let me see.

72
00:05:43,349 --> 00:05:45,751
Did you pass out again?

73
00:05:45,751 --> 00:05:48,720
It's not that. That doesn't happen anymore.

74
00:05:58,064 --> 00:06:00,132
Look at you.

75
00:06:00,132 --> 00:06:03,502
Do you fight with other kids now?

76
00:06:05,505 --> 00:06:06,915
Hey, it's all right.

77
00:06:06,915 --> 00:06:10,208
All boys grow up fighting each other.

78
00:06:10,209 --> 00:06:12,878
I've been there, too.

79
00:06:12,878 --> 00:06:15,047
I said it's not like that.

80
00:06:15,748 --> 00:06:18,894
How did it go, son? Did you get in a punch or two?

81
00:06:18,894 --> 00:06:21,787
[Integrated Science]

82
00:06:25,791 --> 00:06:28,160
All right. Rest up.

83
00:06:28,161 --> 00:06:30,295
What's with you these days?

84
00:06:34,467 --> 00:06:37,503
[Force and acceleration...]

85
00:06:43,509 --> 00:06:48,047
[Force and acceleration...]

86
00:07:42,235 --> 00:07:44,336
Hey, you bastard.

87
00:07:45,872 --> 00:07:47,639
Meet me after class.

88
00:07:47,639 --> 00:07:51,109
I had my guard down yesterday, you sly punk.

89
00:07:51,109 --> 00:07:53,846
You're dead meat today.

90
00:07:59,652 --> 00:08:01,687
Let's get it over with now.

91
00:08:03,289 --> 00:08:04,733
That psycho.

92
00:08:04,733 --> 00:08:07,226
He's a damn punk.

93
00:08:17,170 --> 00:08:18,804
That bastard.

94
00:08:33,152 --> 00:08:34,653
Damn it.

95
00:08:41,928 --> 00:08:46,128
I guess you're both slow learners.

96
00:08:46,733 --> 00:08:49,001
What's that punk saying?

97
00:08:56,242 --> 00:08:58,654
- Gosh.
- What's wrong?

98
00:08:58,654 --> 00:09:00,379
What the heck?

99
00:09:07,653 --> 00:09:09,555
Reviewing is key...

100
00:09:11,257 --> 00:09:13,392
when you have a bad memory.

101
00:09:23,236 --> 00:09:25,537
Pavlov's dog experiment.

102
00:09:29,175 --> 00:09:30,843
You ring the bell.

103
00:09:32,044 --> 00:09:34,212
You feed the dog.

104
00:09:34,212 --> 00:09:36,548
The dog salivates.

105
00:09:38,084 --> 00:09:39,718
You ring the bell.

106
00:09:41,154 --> 00:09:42,955
You feed the dog.

107
00:09:44,423 --> 00:09:46,658
The dog salivates.

108
00:09:51,097 --> 00:09:53,932
Then you only ring the bell.

109
00:09:55,234 --> 00:09:57,069
Let's stop this.

110
00:09:57,069 --> 00:09:58,603
Okay?

111
00:09:59,405 --> 00:10:01,173
I'm asking you nicely.

112
00:10:01,941 --> 00:10:03,541
Got it?

113
00:10:19,392 --> 00:10:22,694
He looks fine. He's not hurt at all.

114
00:10:22,694 --> 00:10:24,706
Hey, Sieun. What happened?

115
00:10:24,706 --> 00:10:27,566
Did you beat up those jerks, too?

116
00:10:34,273 --> 00:10:35,773
Do I know you?

117
00:10:39,612 --> 00:10:41,212
Are we friends?

118
00:11:26,125 --> 00:11:28,927
What's going on? Where is everyone?

119
00:12:02,829 --> 00:12:04,930
I told you to know your limits.

120
00:12:09,202 --> 00:12:10,802
What's this?

121
00:12:13,139 --> 00:12:15,307
Get a nose job while you're here.

122
00:12:21,547 --> 00:12:23,247
So who's the guy?

123
00:12:24,250 --> 00:12:25,850
A kid in my class.

124
00:12:25,850 --> 00:12:27,618
How much are you going to pay?

125
00:12:28,354 --> 00:12:30,122
How much do you want?

126
00:12:31,023 --> 00:12:33,392
Damn. Are you that loaded?

127
00:12:34,727 --> 00:12:37,229
I wish your dad was my dad.

128
00:12:42,502 --> 00:12:44,102
"Help me."

129
00:12:44,737 --> 00:12:46,237
"Hyung."

130
00:12:47,874 --> 00:12:49,574
Say it.

131
00:12:49,574 --> 00:12:51,443
"Help me, Hyung."

132
00:12:53,479 --> 00:12:55,079
Help me.

133
00:12:56,215 --> 00:12:57,715
Hyung.

134
00:13:18,538 --> 00:13:20,749
Hey. What are you doing here?

135
00:13:20,749 --> 00:13:22,785
We keep running into each other.

136
00:13:22,785 --> 00:13:24,410
Where are you going?

137
00:13:25,478 --> 00:13:27,512
I'm going home.

138
00:13:27,512 --> 00:13:29,147
What?

139
00:13:31,150 --> 00:13:32,950
Home.

140
00:13:32,950 --> 00:13:34,820
After academy classes?

141
00:13:34,820 --> 00:13:36,989
- Yes.
- I see.

142
00:13:42,194 --> 00:13:44,062
Sorry about yesterday.

143
00:13:44,096 --> 00:13:45,374
All of a sudden?

144
00:13:45,374 --> 00:13:47,709
Buy me lunch sometime if you're so sorry.

145
00:13:47,709 --> 00:13:50,168
I'm off. See you tomorrow.

146
00:14:12,892 --> 00:14:14,002
I'll take these two.

147
00:14:14,002 --> 00:14:15,828
Your delivery's here!

148
00:14:17,129 --> 00:14:18,897
Your delivery's here!

149
00:14:32,445 --> 00:14:33,756
Here's your delivery.

150
00:14:33,756 --> 00:14:36,415
- Do you want some candy?
- Yes.

151
00:14:37,617 --> 00:14:39,218
Don't tell anyone.

152
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:55,430
♫ Baby, I don't know how to go home, now I'm sick ♫

153
00:14:55,430 --> 00:14:59,039
♫ Looking for shoes for my dead feet ♫

154
00:14:59,039 --> 00:15:02,675
[English: Study vacabulary for finals]
♫ I hear the second hand late, replying to me each time ♫

155
00:15:02,675 --> 00:15:06,446
♫ The news is easy to hear, like a fight ♫

156
00:15:06,446 --> 00:15:10,250
[Byeoksan High School]
♫ Baby, I don't know how to go home, now I'm sick ♫

157
00:15:10,250 --> 00:15:13,830
[Teaching Staff Showers]
♫ Soak my dirty body in the water ♫

158
00:15:13,830 --> 00:15:17,640
♫ I hear the second hand late, replying to me one-by-one ♫

159
00:15:17,640 --> 00:15:21,850
♫ I can hear news easily like a heartbeat ♫

160
00:16:10,109 --> 00:16:11,286
What?

161
00:16:11,286 --> 00:16:14,246
- It's lunchtime.
- Right.

162
00:16:14,246 --> 00:16:16,515
I'm not hungry.

163
00:16:17,083 --> 00:16:18,783
It's my treat.

164
00:16:24,690 --> 00:16:26,525
What's with that face?

165
00:16:27,460 --> 00:16:29,260
No, thanks.

166
00:16:37,603 --> 00:16:40,372
I honestly wasn't expecting much.

167
00:16:40,940 --> 00:16:43,609
But I pay for my own school meals.

168
00:16:43,609 --> 00:16:45,277
Don't eat it then.

169
00:16:48,681 --> 00:16:50,281
Thanks for lunch.

170
00:16:55,888 --> 00:16:57,488
By the way...

171
00:16:58,624 --> 00:17:00,435
- why do you sleep at school?
- That?

172
00:17:00,435 --> 00:17:02,171
I come straight here after work.

173
00:17:02,171 --> 00:17:05,030
Just in case I sleep in at home.

174
00:17:05,031 --> 00:17:09,976
My grandma insists that I graduate with perfect attendance even if I don't go to college.

175
00:17:12,371 --> 00:17:14,973
Do you like listening to music?

176
00:17:15,675 --> 00:17:19,443
You always have earbuds in like an arrogant brat.

177
00:17:21,681 --> 00:17:23,916
- I just can't be bothered.
- What?

178
00:17:24,484 --> 00:17:27,486
I can't be bothered to talk to anyone.

179
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:29,431
You know you're really weird, right?

180
00:17:29,431 --> 00:17:31,590
You're one to talk.

181
00:17:42,235 --> 00:17:45,114
Hey. Why isn't there a disciplinary hearing for Sieun?

182
00:17:45,114 --> 00:17:46,839
I heard that...

183
00:17:46,839 --> 00:17:48,984
Yeongbin got caught with fentanyl.

184
00:17:48,984 --> 00:17:50,819
- Really?
- There's no way.

185
00:17:50,819 --> 00:17:53,622
Seriously. They're letting him off to cover it up.

186
00:17:53,622 --> 00:17:55,824
But why are those two hanging out?

187
00:17:55,824 --> 00:17:58,193
It's like they've become best friends.

188
00:17:58,193 --> 00:18:00,462
I heard Suho is an MMA fighter.

189
00:18:00,462 --> 00:18:02,064
He nearly debuted in the AFC.

190
00:18:02,064 --> 00:18:04,733
So that's why his counterpunch was so satisfying to watch.

191
00:18:04,733 --> 00:18:06,435
Yes, he did throw nice punches.

192
00:18:06,435 --> 00:18:08,337
[Add Money]

193
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:10,196
[6,000,000 won]
[Add Money]

194
00:18:11,531 --> 00:18:12,608
[1,000,000 won]

195
00:18:12,608 --> 00:18:14,533
[2,000,000 WON]

196
00:18:21,374 --> 00:18:23,676
[3,000,000 won]
[Place Bet]

197
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:28,260
[Lose]

198
00:18:33,586 --> 00:18:34,630
[Promissory Note]

199
00:18:34,630 --> 00:18:37,889
I need your fingerprint here, here, and here.

200
00:18:44,564 --> 00:18:46,365
It's a Gucci.

201
00:18:46,966 --> 00:18:48,667
Awesome.

202
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:58,110
[Creditor: Jeon Seokdae]
[Debtor: Kim Wonseok]

203
00:19:01,247 --> 00:19:02,847
It actually works.

204
00:19:02,847 --> 00:19:06,852
When will the money be transferred?

205
00:19:09,121 --> 00:19:10,621
Leave.

206
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:23,202
- You're late.
- So?

207
00:19:23,803 --> 00:19:25,603
Should I be sorry?

208
00:19:29,175 --> 00:19:31,743
- Nothing's fun.
- They're my friends.

209
00:19:31,743 --> 00:19:33,511
This is my cousin.

210
00:19:33,511 --> 00:19:35,247
He's damn loaded.

211
00:19:36,883 --> 00:19:38,383
What?

212
00:19:39,719 --> 00:19:41,687
What are you staring at?

213
00:19:41,687 --> 00:19:43,655
You look like crap.

214
00:19:43,655 --> 00:19:45,223
Me?

215
00:19:45,223 --> 00:19:47,859
That was cruel.

216
00:19:51,164 --> 00:19:52,564
Hey.

217
00:19:54,167 --> 00:19:55,934
When will he get here?

218
00:20:02,208 --> 00:20:03,608
Sieun.

219
00:20:04,310 --> 00:20:05,910
Hey, Sieun.

220
00:20:08,748 --> 00:20:10,683
Are you also done with school?

221
00:20:10,683 --> 00:20:12,518
Are you going to an academy?

222
00:20:13,219 --> 00:20:14,619
Yes.

223
00:20:14,619 --> 00:20:16,688
Which academy do you go to?

224
00:20:17,690 --> 00:20:19,290
Daemyung Academy.

225
00:20:19,859 --> 00:20:22,337
I should start looking for an academy.

226
00:20:22,337 --> 00:20:23,572
Do you like yours?

227
00:20:23,572 --> 00:20:25,630
Should I join, too?

228
00:20:33,172 --> 00:20:35,741
There's no need to suck up to me.

229
00:20:35,741 --> 00:20:38,277
And I won't accept your apology.

230
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:49,598
Come on. Hurry up.

231
00:20:49,598 --> 00:20:51,657
Let's speed it up.

232
00:20:52,525 --> 00:20:55,193
- Meet me after this.
- Damn!

233
00:20:57,396 --> 00:20:59,431
- You startled me.
- Jeez.

234
00:21:00,199 --> 00:21:02,434
What? Is class over?

235
00:21:02,434 --> 00:21:03,545
Yes.

236
00:21:03,545 --> 00:21:06,115
Damn. I feel like a loner. My feelings are hurt.

237
00:21:06,115 --> 00:21:10,175
- Did any of you even think to wake me?
- You told us not to.

238
00:21:11,744 --> 00:21:13,744
Did I?

239
00:21:13,746 --> 00:21:15,914
Wake me up in ten minutes.

240
00:21:49,182 --> 00:21:50,225
Is this the guy?

241
00:21:50,225 --> 00:21:52,561
Gosh, seriously?

242
00:21:52,561 --> 00:21:55,821
Aren't you embarrassed? This is so wrong.

243
00:22:01,928 --> 00:22:04,062
I have to go to an academy.

244
00:22:04,062 --> 00:22:05,964
I have nothing against you.

245
00:22:06,866 --> 00:22:09,134
Sorry, but this is just business.

246
00:22:24,450 --> 00:22:26,028
Is that Yeongbin's crew?

247
00:22:26,028 --> 00:22:29,488
- So damn intimidating.
- They look scary as hell.

248
00:22:30,523 --> 00:22:32,501
Shouldn't we tell our teacher?

249
00:22:32,501 --> 00:22:35,560
He's right. I heard Youngbin's cousin...

250
00:22:46,772 --> 00:22:48,172
An Suho.

251
00:22:50,042 --> 00:22:51,542
An Suho.

252
00:22:53,412 --> 00:22:56,181
Yeongbin dragged Sieun away.

253
00:22:56,182 --> 00:22:57,782
What?

254
00:22:57,782 --> 00:23:00,429
Jeon Yeongbin dragged Sieun off somewhere.

255
00:23:00,429 --> 00:23:02,253
So what?

256
00:23:02,253 --> 00:23:04,155
What?

257
00:23:04,155 --> 00:23:06,835
Help me. We should help him.

258
00:23:06,835 --> 00:23:09,428
You were a fighter, weren't you?

259
00:23:09,428 --> 00:23:11,697
I'm not that close to him.

260
00:23:12,698 --> 00:23:15,668
How close do you need to be to help a friend out?

261
00:23:15,668 --> 00:23:17,736
Just go get our teacher.

262
00:23:17,736 --> 00:23:19,571
I have a part-time job.

263
00:23:20,573 --> 00:23:22,608
I'll pay you.

264
00:23:26,579 --> 00:23:28,547
I'll pay double your wage.

265
00:23:37,390 --> 00:23:38,801
Thank you very much, sir.

266
00:23:38,801 --> 00:23:40,425
Let's go, sir.

267
00:23:41,027 --> 00:23:43,195
Let's get going, sir!

268
00:23:48,334 --> 00:23:50,269
Come on. Jump on.

269
00:24:00,146 --> 00:24:01,946
Look carefully.

270
00:24:24,303 --> 00:24:26,205
Yeongi, keep a lookout.

271
00:24:27,106 --> 00:24:28,806
Seriously?

272
00:24:29,775 --> 00:24:32,121
This is so damn boring.

273
00:24:32,121 --> 00:24:34,480
You're acting like children.

274
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:37,449
