421
00:38:14,009 --> 00:38:16,211
Indeterminate equations.

422
00:38:16,211 --> 00:38:19,281
Why do we call these "indeterminate" equations?

423
00:38:19,281 --> 00:38:21,383
"Unable to determine."

424
00:38:21,383 --> 00:38:24,653
It means that the equations are not determined.

425
00:38:24,653 --> 00:38:26,622
And why is that?

426
00:38:26,622 --> 00:38:30,726
There are many possible solutions, so it's very difficult

427
00:38:30,726 --> 00:38:34,830
to choose one and say that it's the correct solution.

428
00:38:34,830 --> 00:38:38,500
So if we're to define indeterminate equations,

429
00:38:38,500 --> 00:38:42,271
when we compare the number of unknown variables and equations,

430
00:38:42,271 --> 00:38:45,841
if the number of unknown variables is bigger than that of equations,

431
00:38:45,841 --> 00:38:48,434
we call it an indeterminate equation.

